    Improved version of `equation_v1`.

    Models acceleration y as a function of time (x0), position (x1), and velocity (x2),
    including physically meaningful linear and nonlinear stiffness and damping terms,
    plus possible time-dependent forcing and higher order nonlinear interactions.

    Parameters:
    - params: array of 12 parameters
        params[0]: constant offset (external forcing)
        params[1]: linear time coefficient (time-dependent forcing)
        params[2]: linear stiffness coefficient (position) [restoring force]
        params[3]: linear damping coefficient (velocity)
        params[4]: cubic stiffness coefficient (position^3)
        params[5]: quadratic velocity damping coefficient (velocity^2)
        params[6]: quadratic position term coefficient
        params[7]: cross term coefficient between position and velocity
        params[8]: quadratic time effect
        params[9]: mixed time-position cubic term
        params[10]: mixed time-velocity quadratic term
        params[11]: higher order mixed nonlinear interaction term

    Returns:
    - y: acceleration array
    """

