    """Equation to be evolved.

    Background:
    Calculate Acceleration in Nonl-linear Harmonic Oscillator given Time, Position at time t and Velocity at time t

    Variables:
    - Independents: x0, x1, x2
- Dependent: y

    Parameters:
    - params (np.ndarray): Trainable coefficients used by the equation skeleton.
    """
    """Improved version of `equation_v1`.

    Calculate acceleration y of a nonlinear harmonic oscillator given:
    - time (x0)
    - position (x1)
    - velocity (x2)

    Model includes:
    - Constant offset
    - Linear time-dependent forcing
    - Linear restoring force (-k * x1)
    - Linear viscous damping (-c * x2)
    - Cubic stiffness nonlinearity (-alpha * x1^3 or + depending on sign)
    - Quadratic velocity damping term (d * v |v|)
    - Quadratic position nonlinearity
    - Cross coupling between position and velocity
    - Time squared parametric excitation
    - Mixed time-position cubic term
    - Mixed time-velocity quadratic term
    - Higher order mixed nonlinearities

    Parameters:
        params[0]: constant offset
        params[1]: linear time coefficient (forcing)
        params[2]: linear stiffness coefficient magnitude (>0), restoring force applied as negative sign
        params[3]: linear damping coefficient magnitude (>0), damping applied as negative sign
        params[4]: cubic stiffness coefficient (sign flexible)
        params[5]: quadratic velocity damping coefficient (sign flexible), modeled as v*|v|
        params[6]: quadratic position term coefficient (sign flexible)
        params[7]: cross term coefficient between position and velocity (sign flexible)
        params[8]: quadratic time effect coefficient (sign flexible)
        params[9]: mixed time-position cubic term coefficient (sign flexible)
