    Models acceleration y as a function of time (x0), position (x1), and velocity (x2),
    incorporating nonlinear stiffness, nonlinear damping, cross terms,
    and periodic forcing with sine and cosine components.

    Equation form:
        y = p0 
            + p1 * x0                   # linear time dependence
            + p2 * x1                   # linear restoring force term (-k*x)
            + p3 * x1**3                # cubic nonlinearity in position (Duffing term)
            + p4 * x2                   # linear damping term (-c*v)
            + p5 * x2**3                # nonlinear damping term
